    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-29T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-29T07:00:00-05:00" n="774"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/11163</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Sebastian</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-29T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 30, 1.55 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1743. Late yesterday afternoon Prime Minister summoned all Ministers, diplomats
                    absent to come to Madrid immediately for council to be held there today. They
                    declined to give any information as to reason for this sudden meeting. Embassy
                    has just learned that Spanish ship <hi rend="italic">Carasa</hi> which left
                    Bilbao for Cardiff with cargo of minerals on August 19, has been torpedoed. Six
                    victims, no further details known at present. News of first sinking doubtless
                    known to Spanish Government yesterday and was reason for council. In view of
                    recent Spanish note to Germany (1708, August 22, 2 p.m., and 1725, August 29
                        [<hi rend="italic">25</hi>], 10 a.m.), a very grave situation has
                    arisen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
